answers.body_markdown:
getMetadata is asynchronous and always returns immediately.  You have to capture errors in the callback on the Task object it returns.  Use the [documentation][1] as your guide:

```
storageRef.getMetadata().addOnSuccessListener(new OnSuccessListener&lt;StorageMetadata&gt;() {
    @Override
    public void onSuccess(StorageMetadata storageMetadata) {
        // Metadata now contains the metadata for &#39;images/forest.jpg&#39;
    }
}).addOnFailureListener(new OnFailureListener() {
    @Override
    public void onFailure(@NonNull Exception exception) {
        // Uh-oh, an error occurred!
    }
});
```

You will not be able to use try/catch.  You must use the failure callback.

  [1]: https://firebase.google.com/docs/storage/android/file-metadata#get_file_metadata

